#
# Custom pytorch dev base recipe: xomoxcc/dgx-spark-pytorch-dev:2.12.0-v1-cu132
#
# Purpose: build the CUDA 13.2.1 + PyTorch 2.12.0 base image. Successor to
# pytorch-2.11.0-dev-v1.recipe — same overall structure, version bumps only.
#
# Delta vs pytorch-2.11.0-dev-v1.recipe:
#   - CUDA_VERSION 13.2.0 -> 13.2.1
#       Plain patch bump on the same minor; identical cuDNN/cuBLAS generation.
#       The nvidia/cuda:13.2.1-devel-ubuntu22.04 image is published on Docker Hub.
#   - TORCH_VERSION 2.11.0 -> 2.12.0
#       2.12.0 highlights relevant to our GB10/sm_121 cluster:
#         * PR #175344  cuBLAS Blackwell 32 MiB workspaces (direct sm_120/121 win)
#         * torch.accelerator.Graph unifies graph capture across CUDA/XPU/etc.
#         * torch.cond control-flow can be captured into CUDA Graphs
#         * Microscaling (MX) quantization formats can be exported via torch.export
#         * Adagrad gained fused=True (matches Adam/AdamW/SGD)
#       Breaking changes worth knowing for THIS image build:
#         * C++20 minimum enforced in CMake (Ubuntu 22.04 gcc-11 is fine)
#         * Stricter SVE-config checks in FindARM.cmake — on ARM (Spark) the
#           toolchain SVE flags must accurately describe the target. If the
#           build fails at the CMake-configure stage on SVE, either fix the
#           gcc -march flags or pass -DCMAKE_DISABLE_FIND_PACKAGE_ARM=ON.
#         * Source builds now require CUDA >= 12.6 (we're on 13.2.1, fine).
#   - TORCH_AUDIO_VERSION 2.11.0 -> 2.11.0   (NO BUMP — torchaudio 2.12.0 was
#       not published yet at recipe-create time (2026-05-29). pytorch/audio
#       still tags v2.11.0 latest; PyPI same. Audio typically lags torch core
#       by 1-2 weeks. Bump to 2.12.0 once it ships. ABI mismatch with torch
#       2.12.0 is harmless for SGLang text-only inference — audio module is
#       never imported. Vision 0.27.0 strict-requires torch==2.12.0 (PyPI
#       requires_dist), so vision is the lockstep canary; audio isn't.
#   - TORCH_VISION_VERSION 0.26.0 -> 0.27.0  (lockstep w/ torch 2.12.0)
#   - IMAGE_TAG :2.11.0-v1-cu132 -> :2.12.0-v1-cu132
#   - NCCL: zyang-dev/nccl#dgxspark-3node-ring 2.29.7-1 -> NVIDIA/nccl v2.30.4-1
#       (newest full release). We previously held the fork, believing its sole
#       commit ("Support 3 DGX Sparks in a ring topology via CX-7") was load-
#       bearing. Reviewing the diff (+141/-0 in src/transport/net_ib/connect.cc)
#       shows it is actually a DEFAULT-OFF "subnet-aware routing" feature gated by
#       NCCL_PARAM(IbSubnetAwareRouting, "IB_SUBNET_AWARE_ROUTING", 0): on connect
#       it picks a local RoCE NIC on the remote peer's IP subnet. It targets
#       MULTI-subnet direct-connect RoCE rings (each link a separate /24, no
#       switch). Verified no-op for us, four ways: (1) we never set the env var
#       (default 0 -> dead code); (2) our QSFP fabric is a single /24
#       (10.10.10.0/24) so every peer shares the subnet -> returns the default
#       device unchanged; (3) we run over a real switch (CRS812), not a direct
#       ring; (4) we pin one HCA (NCCL_IB_MERGE_NICS=0), so there is nothing to
#       re-select. The patch's own comments call it inert for "single-subnet" and
#       "switch" setups. Upstream loses us nothing and tracks current NCCL. Sanity
#       check post-build with the nccl_test framework (k8s_dgx tag nccl_test,
#       roce variant) — not because we expect breakage, just the usual minor-bump
#       diligence (2.29 -> 2.30).
#   - [2026-07-06] NCCL v2.30.4-1 -> v2.30.7-1 — patch bump, newest tag on
#     NVIDIA/nccl as of this check (github.com/NVIDIA/nccl/tags; next-newest
#     after 2.30.7-1 is 2.30.4-1 itself, so no versions were skipped). Same
#     minor (2.30.x) as the already-adopted mainline switch above — no new
#     re-verification of the subnet-aware-routing no-op analysis needed.
#     Re-run nccl_test (k8s_dgx tag nccl_test, roce variant) after rebuild as
#     the usual minor-bump diligence.
#
# Deliberately unchanged:
#   - TORCH_CUDA_ARCH_LIST / NVCC_GENCODE: Spark-target arches (sm_120 + sm_121).
#   - BUILD_JOBS: 8 is the safe ceiling on GB10 (see feedback_build_jobs_gb10).
#
# Follow-up after this image builds successfully:
#   - sglang-0.5.12-sm121.recipe BASE_IMAGE line (currently pinned to
#     xomoxcc/dgx-spark-pytorch-dev:2.11.0-v1-cu132) needs to be bumped to
#     :2.12.0-v1-cu132 in lockstep, otherwise the SGLang image continues to
#     pull the old PyTorch base.
#
DOCKERFILE=Dockerfile.base
TARGET=pytorch_builder

CUDA_VERSION=13.2.1
CUDA_SHORT=132

NCCL_VERSION=2.30.7-1
NCCL_REF=v2.30.7-1
NCCL_REPO=https://github.com/NVIDIA/nccl.git

BUILD_JOBS=8

#TORCH_CUDA_ARCH_LIST=12.1a
#NVCC_GENCODE=-gencode=arch=compute_121,code=sm_121
TORCH_CUDA_ARCH_LIST="12.0;12.1"
NVCC_GENCODE="-gencode=arch=compute_120,code=sm_120 -gencode=arch=compute_121,code=sm_121"

TORCH_VERSION=2.12.0
# torchaudio 2.12.0 not released yet (PyPI latest = 2.11.0 as of 2026-05-29).
# Bump when pytorch/audio tags v2.12.0. Safe for SGLang text-only.
TORCH_AUDIO_VERSION=2.11.0
TORCH_VISION_VERSION=0.27.0

IMAGE_TAG=xomoxcc/dgx-spark-pytorch-dev:2.12.0-v1-cu132
